09:42 AM  Defendant Jerry L. Williams in court.  Attorney Jason Daniel Baltz in court for Jerry L. Williams.  Attorney Angelina R Scarpelli in court for State of Wisconsin. 
State moves to amend the sole count to Battery, contrary to Wis. Stat. 940.19(1), a class A misdemeanor. Motion granted. 
Count 1, Misdemeanor Battery, No contest plea entered. Rights explained. Convicted.
Sentence withheld. Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for one (1) years.  
Conditions of probation:
1)	Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2)	No contact with A.W. unless permitted by agent;
3)	Comply with any DHS recommendations;
4)	Maintain fulltime employment, schooling, or combination;
5)	Attend parenting classes and follow through;
6)	Pay court costs;
7)	Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
8)	Submit to a DNA sample.
Minutes.
